(There is a moment in any performance where the impossible becomes visible. Not the reveal) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
72.0 540.0 Td
(? the moment before it. The moment when the audience has been brought to the precise edge) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
72.0 526.0 Td
(of what their predictive system can hold before it fails. That moment is not an accident.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
72.0 512.0 Td
(It is an engineering problem, and the material you are working with is the human brain.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
72.0 494.0 Td
(Right now, reading this sentence, your brain is predicting how it ends. Every brain in) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
72.0 480.0 Td
(your audience is doing the same thing, constantly: generating predictions about what is) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
72.0 466.0 Td
(about to happen, then comparing those predictions to what actually occurs. The gap) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
72.0 452.0 Td
(between prediction and reality is where experience lives. Wonder is not what happens when) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
72.0 438.0 Td
(something impossible occurs. Wonder is what happens when the prediction fails at a moment) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
72.0 424.0 Td
(of maximum confidence, in a context the nervous system has already decided is safe. You) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
72.0 410.0 Td
(just experienced a micro-version of it. The sentence did not end where you expected.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
72.0 392.0 Td
(This book is about engineering those conditions deliberately.) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 11 Tf
